rComments: One of the best professors Ive had at U of T. He is very knowledgeable about the content. Knows how to engage with the class. He is very quirky with his jokes which makes the learning atmosphere much more fun. Keep up the good work Prof!

Simon's lectures are always fun to attend. We typically start off with a debate or group activity of some kind, so you're forced to do the readings if you want your participation mark. His teaching style is relaxed and fun though, with a lot of room for debate and questions. His marking was a bit tough for the midterm. All in all, would take again.
